\begin{frame}{ Simulation and Reconstruction}
\begin{itemize}
 \item Events are generated with a particle gun and simulated using GEANT4 and the LArSoft toolkit. 
 \item Muons are generated and propagated horizontally and lengthwise of the detector geometry proposed for the single-phase DUNE-FD.
 \item Angle are uniformly varies from 1 to 11$^{\circ}$ ($\theta_{ xz \& yz }$=6 $\pm$ 5). % _{$\&$ YX }$ =  .
\item X and Y coordinates are also uniformly varied from -500 to 500 cm while Z is kept fixed at 0.0. 
 \item 10000 events are generated at each energy value : 100 GeV to 50 TeV.  
 \item The energy deposited by the track is estimated from drifting ionization charge that is collected by anode wires. 
 \item Charge on wires is reconstructed as hits. Hits associated between planes allow the reconstruction of three-dimensional space points.
\end{itemize}
\end{frame}

